> Article 32 A work that has been [published] may be [quoted] and used. In this case, the quotation shall be in conformity with fair practice and within the scope justifiable for the purpose of news reporting, criticism, research and other quotations.
> 2 Public relations materials, research and statistical materials, reports, and other similar works prepared by a national or local government agency, an incorporated administrative agency, or a local incorporated administrative agency for the purpose of making them generally known and published under the name of such works may be reproduced in newspapers, magazines, and other publications as explanatory material. (2) The following provisions shall apply to the reproduction of such works. However, this shall not apply where there is a notice prohibiting such reproduction.
